# Services (`kiki/services/`)

## Responsibility

Network calls, pagination, file output, command_summary parsing. **No FastMCP imports.**

## Virus (gget)

- Map filters via `virus_kwargs()` / `metadata_kwargs()` in `filters.py`
- Full pagination before returning counts or previews
- Dataset: parse `command_summary.txt` failures; never hide partial failures

## UniProt

- Base URL: `https://rest.uniprot.org` (`kiki/config.py`)
- Search pagination via `Link: rel="next"` cursor headers
- ID mapping: run → poll status → results (handle status payload variants)

## Ensembl

- Direct client: `kiki/services/ensembl.py` (REST + pinned public SQL + FTP URLs)
- Always resolve release via `resolve_ensembl_release()` — default `KIKI_ENSEMBL_RELEASE` (114)
- Archived REST host: `https://e{release}.rest.ensembl.org` — per-ID GET lookups (no batch POST)
- Search uses Ensembl public MySQL against the pinned release core database

## NCBI E-utilities (genome / nucleotide)

- Client: `kiki/services/ncbi_eutils.py` — `efetch`, `esummary`, assembly `esearch`+`esummary`
- Direct accession path for GenBank/RefSeq (`NC_*`, etc.) and GCF/GCA assemblies
- Enforce `NCBI_EUTILS_MIN_INTERVAL` (default 0.34s) between requests; optional `NCBI_API_KEY` for higher limits
- Filtered viral taxon queries remain on gget virus tools

## NCBI BLAST (URL API)

- Client: `kiki/services/ncbi_blast.py` — `CMD=Put` submit, `CMD=Get` status + JSON2 results
- Two MCP tools: `submit_blast_search`, `get_blast_results` (poll once per call)
- v1 allowlist: `core_nt`, `refseq_rna`, `swissprot`, `refseq_protein` — not `nt`/`nr`
- Enforce `NCBI_BLAST_MIN_INTERVAL` (default 3s); optional `NCBI_API_KEY`, `NCBI_BLAST_EMAIL`
- 50 KB inline FASTA cap; RIDs ephemeral (~24h) — document in tool docstrings

Use `resolve_writable_dir()` / `output_root()` — hosted `/app` is read-only; fallback `/tmp/kiki_*`.

## Errors

Raise `KikiError(ErrorCode.UPSTREAM_ERROR, ...)` for API failures; `NOT_FOUND` for 404 accessions.
